also<br>
<br>
&quot;What was Iraq hiding? Documentation primarily - documents that would enable them to reconstitute - at a future date - weapons of mass destruction capability....But all of this is useless...unless Iraq has access to the tens, if not hundreds, of millions of dollars required to rebuild the industrial infrastructure (necessary) to build these weapons.&quot;<br>
<br>
OMG, let's connect the dots folks.  Iraq still has some unaccounted WMD.  Iraq is required by the UN to be 100% disarmed, not 75%, not 90%.  Iraq has the knowledge to build more WMD.  France would willingly give money to Saddem in exchange for oil. Even if France doesn't give Saddem money, Saddem can still rebuild his own plants and mobile chemical flatbed trucks that are hidden in the desert in the years since the UN inspectors were kicked.<br>
<br>
Knowledge is power, let's not forget that.  You can rebuild whatever has been destroyed with time, power, money, and knowledge.  And I don't want Scott Ritter's OPINION.  I want the facts.  Saddem has no right nor position of power to play games and ask for sanctions to be lifted when he's not in full compliance. Saddem you desert rat arse bastard, you comply with the UN and it's demands or we'll see you on the battlefield.  And we'll see about those sanctions when we're ready.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Quote from Taranna<br>
